The paper deals with medium access control mechanisms and collision recovery in wireless networks, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed ACK mechanism involves combining collision recovery methods with network coding, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses delay and throughput performance, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
